senses.sense: The Himalayan tahr, Hemitragus jemlahicus ( <= Capra jemlaica).
(India) A pond, marsh, lake or similar wetland area, usually with significant vegetation providing shelter and/or food to a variety of aquatic and semi-aquatic animal species.
(India) The saddlecloth, housings or trappings for an elephant, horse, or other domesticated animal.
(East India) A species of grassy tamarisk shrub, Tamarix indica, common in river-marshes.
